rcraft Transactions:**\n    *   Maintenance of a SpaceX-owned aircraft by **Craft Aviation Services, LLC** (Musk affiliate): **$1M (2023), $1M (2024), $3M (2025), $1M (Jan-Feb 2026).**\n    *   SpaceX incurred expenses when Musk used his personal aircraft for business: **$0.1M (2023), $3M (2024), $2M (2025), $0.2M (Jan-Feb 2026).**\n*   **Stock Purchases:** In 2025, Musk purchased **$1,421 million** of SpaceX common stock.\n\n#### **B. Transactions with Antonio J. Gracias & Valor Equity Partners**\n*   **Major Equipment Leases (AI Infrastructure Hardware):**\n    *   Three separate lease agreements with aggregate cash payments over the life of each lease of **$6,986M, $6,633M, and $6,587M**.\n    *   **Total Payments:** **$885M (2025), $857M (Jan-Feb 2026).**\n    *   **Accounting Treatment:** Deemed **failed sale-leaseback transactions**, recorded as debt.\n    *   **Balance Sheet Impact (Mar 31, 2026):** Debt of **$1,121M (current)** and **$7,920M (non-current)**.\n    *   **Interest Expense (Q1 2026):** **$186M**.\n*   **API Service Payments:** X received payments from Valor for API services: **$1M (2024), $1M (2025), $0.1M (Jan-Feb 2026).**\n\n#### **C. Transactions with Tesla, Inc.**\n*   **Purchases of Megapack Energy Storage & Vehicles:**\n    *   **Megapacks:** **$191M (2024), $506M (2025), $34M (Q1 2026).**\n    *   **Cybertrucks:** **$131M (2025).**\n*   **Tesla's Investment in xAI:** Tesla invested **$2,000M** in xAI via Series E Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock.\n    *   **Post-Merger Conversion:** This investment converted into the right to acquire **3.8 million shares of SpaceX Class A Common Stock** (pre-split), issued in March 2026.\n\n#### **D. Aircraft Use by Other Directors & Officers**\n*   Gwynne Shotwell and Bret Johnsen occasionally used their co-owned aircraft for SpaceX business when company aircraft were unavailable, subject to reimbursement.\n\n---\n\n### **IV. Accounting & Presentation of Related-Party Mergers**\n*   **Common Control Mergers:** The acquisitions of xAI and X by SpaceX were accounted for as reorganizations under **common control** (due to Elon Musk's controlling interest).\n*   **Retrospective Adjustment:** Financial statements for all periods presented have been **retrospectively recast** to combine the net assets and results of SpaceX, xAI, and X at historical carrying amounts.\n*   **Elimination of Intercompany Transactions:** All historical related-party transactions **between the merged entities** have been eliminated in consolidation.\n*   **Change in Reporting Entity:** This retrospective combination constitutes a change in reporting entity.\n*   **2026 Stock Split:** A five-for-one forward stock split effective May 4, 2026, has been retroactively applied to all share and per-share data.\n\n---\n\n### **V. Legal Proceedings Involving Related Parties**\n*   **NAACP vs. X.AI Corp & MZX Tech, LLC:** Lawsuit alleging Clean Air Act violations related to mobile gas turbines powering the **COLOSSUS II** data center (affiliated with xAI). A preliminary injunction motion has been filed.\n\n---\n\n### **VI. Summary of Financial Impact**\n*   **Major Balance Sheet Items:**\n    *   **Debt to Valor:** ~**$9.04 billion** (current + non-current) as of Mar 31, 2026.\n    *   **Litigation Accrual:** **$399 million** recorded as of Mar 31, 2026.\n*   **Significant Cash Flows:**\n    *   Payments to Valor for leases: **$1.74 billion** in the 14-month period ending Feb 28, 2026.\n    *   Payments to Tesla for products: Over **$800 million** in 2024-2026 (YTD).\n    *   Cash paid in xAI Merger: **$2.947 billion**.\n\n**Note:** All data is sourced from the provided excerpts and reflects the combined entity following the common-control mergers.",
