        output='Based on the provided excerpts from SpaceX\'s financial statements and prospectus, here is a summary of the discussions regarding pre-merger intercompany activity between SpaceX, xAI, and X Holdings.\n\n### 1. Accounting Treatment & General Disclosure of Elimination\nThe financial statements repeatedly explain that because the mergers were accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control (all controlled by Elon Musk), the consolidated financial statements were prepared through a **retrospective combination** of the entities\' historical net assets.\n\n**Key points from the preamble and notes:**\n*   **Historical Carrying Amounts:** The net assets of xAI and X were combined at their historical carrying amounts, meaning no new goodwill or intangible assets were recognized.\n*   **Elimination of Transactions:** A critical part of this retrospective consolidation was the elimination of all historical transactions between the entities. The statements explicitly state: **"all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation"** and **"All intercompany balances and transactions have been eliminated in consolidation."**\n*   **Change in Reporting Entity:** This presentation is considered a change in reporting entity, and as a result, separate financial statements for xAI and X are not provided.\n\n### 2. Specific Pre-Merger Intercompany Transactions (Detailed Disclosures)\nThe most detailed disclosures of the specific pre-merger intercompany activity are found in the **"Certain Relationships and Related Person Transactions"** section. This section itemizes transactions that occurred between the entities (and their affiliates) prior to the mergers, which were subsequently eliminated upon consolidation.\n\n**Disclosed transaction types include:**\n\n*   **Commercial & Licensing Agreements:**\n    *   **SpaceX with Tesla:** Obtained goods and services under commercial agreements. (Amounts cited for