    final_answer='## Related-Party Relationships and Pre-Merger Intercompany Activity in the SpaceX Consolidated Structure\n\n### Overview of Consolidated Structure\n\nFollowing the common-control mergers — X Holdings into xAI on March 28, 2025, and xAI into SpaceX on February 2, 2026 — the consolidated entity encompasses SpaceX, xAI, X Holdings (X), and X.AI Corp. The filings treat these entities as components of a single economic unit under Elon Musk\'s controlling financial interest throughout all historical periods presented. All financial statements have been retrospectively recast under common-control accounting.\n\n---\n\n### Related-Party Relationships Within the Consolidated Structure\n\nThe filing identifies several layers of related-party relationships:\n\n**1. Elon Musk (Founder, CEO, CTO, Chairman & Principal Shareholder)**\n- Controls SpaceX, xAI, and X through majority voting interest\n- Also CEO, Technoking, director, and ~20% shareholder of Tesla\n- Transactions with SpaceX include: security services ($2M–$4M annually, 2023–2025), aircraft usage reimbursements, and $1,421M in stock purchases in 2025\n\n**2. Affiliated Musk Entities**\n- **Musk Industries LLC**: Lease payments from xAI for office space ($0.5M in 2024, $2M in 2025)\n- **The Boring Company**: Lease payments from X ($0.1M in 2024, $1M in 2025); construction services for SpaceX ($1M in 2025)\n- **Craft Aviation Services, LLC**: Aircraft maintenance for SpaceX ($1M–$3M annually, 2023–2025)\n\n**3. Antonio J. Gracias & Valor Equity Partners**\n- Gracias is a SpaceX board member and founder/CEO/CIO of Valor Equity Partners\n- Three major equipment (AI infrastructure hardware) lease agreements with aggregate cash payments of $6,986M, $6,633M, and $6,587M over the lease terms\n- Total lease payments: $885M (2025), $857M (Jan–Feb 2026)\n- Classified as **failed sale-leaseback transactions** and recorded as debt: ~$1,121M (current) and ~$7,920M (non-current) as of March 31, 2026\n- API service payments from X to Valor: $1M (2024), $1M (2025)\n\n**4. Tesla, Inc.**\n- Tesla invested **$2,000M** in xAI via Series E Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, which converted into the right to acquire 3.8 million SpaceX Class A Common Shares (pre-split) post-merger\n- SpaceX purchased Tesla Megapacks ($191M in 2024, $506M in 2025, $34M in Q1 2026) and Cybertrucks ($131M in 2025)\n- Tesla purchased advertising on the X platform ($4M in 2025)\n- SpaceX invoiced Tesla for Musk\'s aircraft usage\n\n**5. Gwynne Shotwell & Bret Johnsen**\n- President/COO and CFO who co-own a personal aircraft; occasionally used for SpaceX business subject to reimbursement\n\n---\n\n### Where the Filing Discusses Pre-Merger Intercompany Activity\n\n**1. Note 1 — Nature of Business / Business Combinations**\n- Describes the X Holdings merger into xAI (March 28, 2025): X Holdings shares converted at a 2.776:1 ratio into xAI shares; X and X.AI Corp. became wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI\n- Describes the xAI merger into SpaceX (February 2, 2026): SpaceX issued 321.7M Class A shares, 121.7M Class B shares, and $2,947M in cash to xAI stockholders\n- Explains common-control accounting: net assets combined at historical carrying amounts with no goodwill recognized\n- States: "all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation"\n\n**2. Note 2 — Summary of Significant Accounting Policies**\n- Reaffirms the broad principle: "All intercompany balances and transactions have been eliminated in consolidation"\n- Notes this constitutes a "change in reporting entity" with retrospective restatement of all periods\n\n**3. "Certain Relationships and Related Person Transactions" Section**\n- This is the primary location for the **detailed enumeration** of specific pre-merger intercompany activity\n- Itemizes all transactions between the consolidated entities and their affiliates, including commercial agreements, leases, services, and asset usage\n- Reports dollar amounts by year (2023, 2024, 2025, and Jan–Feb 2026) for each category\n- Threshold disclosure: transactions exceeding $120,000 since January 1, 2023\n- Scope includes all transactions involving directors, executive officers, >5% stockholders, and their affiliates\n\n**4. Note 12/13 — Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock & Shareholders\' Equity**\n- Details the conversion mechanics of xAI redeemable convertible preferred stock into SpaceX shares at a 0.1433 exchange ratio\n- Documents Tesla\'s $2B xAI investment and its post-merger conversion into SpaceX equity\n- Covers the full capital stock and equity adjustments from the mergers\n\n**5. Share-Based Compensation Note**\n- Details conversion of xAI and X employee stock options and RSUs into SpaceX awards using the exchange ratios (0.1433 for xAI, 2.776 for X)\n\n---\n\n### Key Accounting Implications\n\n- **No separate entity financials provided**: Because of the retrospective common-control presentation, standalone financial statements for xAI and X are not available\n- **Eliminated intercompany balances**: The filing does not provide a line-by-line breakdown of specific intercompany receivables/payables that were eliminated; they are netted within the combined historical figures\n- **Implicit pre-merger integration**: The common-control framework implies the entities operated as part of a single economic unit prior to formal mergers, with financial activities structured as internal transfers within the Musk-controlled group\n\n---\n\n### Sources\n\n| Source | URL |\n|--------|-----|\n| SpaceX S-1 Filing (May 20, 2026) | https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm |',
